[{"location":"#Tree-1","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Getting-started-1","page":"Tree","title":"Getting started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"It's a simple as creating and instance of the app, adding a route then starting the server","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"app = App()\n\napp(\"/path\"; method = GET) do request\n    # your code here\n    reponse = \"hello\"\n    return response\nend\n\nstart(app)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"The response can be of any type however if you need more control you can overload create_response for specific types.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"create_response(t::Mytype)::Response","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"This defined for AbstractString and Dict already.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Routing-and-Query-Parameters-1","page":"Tree","title":"Routing and Query Parameters","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Routes can be defined for multiple methods by passing an array","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"app(handler, \"/path\", [GET, POST])","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Routes can be parametrized by using the syntax /:x. You can then access the parameters the handler.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"app(\"/route/:id\"; method = [GET, POST]) do request\n    params = path_params(request)\n    # Dict(:id => value)\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Query parameters can be accessed in a similar way","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"query = query_params(request)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Specific routes like /path take priority over variable routes such as /:path.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Sessions-1","page":"Tree","title":"Sessions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"When instantiating the app you can pass any data structure you want to use for the session, by default this will be a Dict. The session can then be accessed in the handler.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"app(\"/path\") do req\n    session = app.session\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#Middleware-1","page":"Tree","title":"Middleware","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Currently not implemented","category":"page"},{"location":"#WebSockest-1","page":"Tree","title":"WebSockest","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Tree","title":"Tree","text":"Currently not implemented","category":"page"}]
